With a powerful roar, that while not anywhere near as powerful as the
previous one still managed to shatter a few of the remaining windows. The
lion leaped off the perch he had been on and began to run at Trelos. If the
large mecha-lion was aware of the grenade launchers that were at his
shoulders, or the fact that he had any other modes or weapons, he was
certainly not using them. Instead he bared his teeth and then roared again
as he ran to battle!

Seeing the Lion charging at him only made Trelos more thirsty for blood.
His already-fast pace turning to frantic as he made dog-like growls and
snorts.  As he got within range, he lept into the air with his powerful hind
legs and attempting to bite down on any part of his enemy that he could get
ahold of.

Meanwhile....

The two Maximals were about to retreat when they noticed that the two
enemies were no longer interested in them.

&quot;Depthcharge to base.  It looks like the two enemies have transformed back
into beast mode and are fighting each other.&quot;

&quot;Interesting.&quot; replied Salveo. &quot;Bossman still wants you to retreat.
Ravenchief, please leave a spypod on that building.  We can probably use an
eye on that building.&quot;

Ravenchief planted the small pod then keyed his radio.

&quot;At the very least, we&#39;ll have something interesting to watch tonight.
Start recording!  We&#39;ll be back soon.&quot;

And with that, the two of them jumped off the backside of the building and
took to the air.


